==English==
===Etymology 1===
From ''[[ne]]'' ‘not’ + ''[[a|ā]]'' ‘ever’.

====Adverb====
{{en-adv|-}}

# {{colloquial}} [[not|Not]].
# {{colloquial}} [[no|No]].

===Etymology 2===
Development of Etymology 1, above; compare ''[[nah]]''.

====Interjection====
# {{Geordie}} Used to show disagreement or negation.
#:'' "'''Na''', you are mistaken."''
#:'' "'''Na''', you [[cannet]] watch telly"''
# Used to show agreement with a negative question.
#:''"Divn’t yee like milk?" "''''Na'''"'' (i.e., "Na, A divn’t like milk.")
# {{colloquial}} [[no|No]].

===Etymology 3===
Abbreviations.

===={{initialism}}====
'''na'''

#{{linguistics}} [[noun animate|Noun animate]].

